<codeline lineno="8"><highlight class="comment"><sp/>*<sp/>The<sp/>`AccuracyMetric`<sp/>class,<sp/>implemented<sp/>in<sp/>Cython,<sp/>is<sp/>a<sp/>specialized<sp/>metric<sp/>within<sp/>the<sp/>AnalysisG<sp/>framework<sp/>designed<sp/>for<sp/>comprehensive<sp/>evaluation<sp/>of<sp/>model<sp/>accuracy,<sp/>particularly<sp/>in<sp/>the<sp/>context<sp/>of<sp/>event-level<sp/>predictions.<sp/>It<sp/>extends<sp/>the<sp/>`MetricTemplate`<sp/>class,<sp/>providing<sp/>tailored<sp/>functionalities<sp/>for<sp/>handling<sp/>prediction<sp/>scores,<sp/>truth<sp/>labels,<sp/>and<sp/>generating<sp/>Receiver<sp/>Operating<sp/>Characteristic<sp/>(ROC)<sp/>curves.<sp/>This<sp/>class<sp/>is<sp/>crucial<sp/>for<sp/>assessing<sp/>the<sp/>performance<sp/>of<sp/>machine<sp/>learning<sp/>models<sp/>in<sp/>high-energy<sp/>physics<sp/>analyses.</highlight></codeline>
